data.name: Garlic Butter Shrimp with Coconut Rice
data.quickTastyDescription: Savory garlic butter shrimp served over creamy coconut rice for a tropical twist.
detailedCookingInstructions: Rinse the rice under cold water until the water runs clear.

In a medium saucepan, combine the rice and coconut milk. Add 1 cup of water and a pinch of salt. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat to low, cover, and simmer for 15 minutes or until the rice is tender and the liquid is absorbed.
While the rice is cooking, melt the butter in a large skillet over medium heat.
Add the minced garlic and saut√© for about 1 minute until fragrant but not browned.
Add the shrimp to the skillet, season with salt and pepper, and cook for 2-3 minutes on each side until pink and cooked through.
Squeeze fresh lime juice over the shrimp and stir to combine.
Once the rice is done, fluff it with a fork and serve it on plates topped with garlic butter shrimp. Garnish with fresh cilantro if desired.
